13:08.292 --> 13:11.918
-Kelsie, do you wanna come up?
-Yep.

13:11.918 --> 13:15.167
What happened the other day
has never happened to me before.

13:15.167 --> 13:17.334
And I know you've got
jobs to do tonight,

13:17.334 --> 13:20.709
but your most important
job is this.

13:20.709 --> 13:22.000
Critical...

13:22.000 --> 13:24.167
Any question, like should
I get them up,

13:24.167 --> 13:26.250
the moment you think that,
come and get us up.

13:26.250 --> 13:27.959
If we get anywhere near
the lines

13:27.959 --> 13:29.209
that I've drawn you, that...

13:29.209 --> 13:30.626
Yeah, like... exactly.

13:30.626 --> 13:33.000
Everyone, I think, is
still a little shook

13:33.000 --> 13:34.626
from running aground,

13:34.626 --> 13:38.584
so I was totally expecting
a very thorough walkthrough.

13:38.584 --> 13:40.751
But I know my duties
on night watch...

13:40.751 --> 13:43.584
me and the stars,
and the sunrises.

13:43.584 --> 13:45.125
I'm nervous because
of what's happened.

13:45.125 --> 13:46.626
-Of what happened, yeah.
-Eh?

13:46.626 --> 13:48.626
-Well, you can count on me.
-That cannot happen.

13:48.626 --> 13:50.375
Glenn, I got it...

13:50.375 --> 13:52.167
wake you up if
I'm unsure about anything.

13:52.167 --> 13:54.042
Roger, copy.

13:54.042 --> 13:55.125
-Okay.
-Nope, it won't.

13:55.125 --> 13:56.334
Good.

13:56.334 --> 13:57.375
All right,
see you guys tomorrow.

13:57.375 --> 13:58.459
We're gonna go to bed, too.

13:58.459 --> 14:00.167
Good night.
Sleep well.

14:00.167 --> 14:09.751
-Cheers, thank you.
-Good night.

14:09.751 --> 14:11.751
No, not mine.

14:11.751 --> 14:13.167
Mm!

14:13.167 --> 14:27.125
[laughing]

14:27.125 --> 14:29.292
There's five knots of wind,

14:29.292 --> 14:38.292
so there are some rocks
that come within the line.

14:38.292 --> 14:39.501
I'll be up now.

14:39.501 --> 14:41.667
It's not fun to
wake the boss up,

14:41.667 --> 14:50.501
but I'd rather wake the boss up
than disobey the boss.

14:50.501 --> 14:52.792
Thank God nothing's
happening, the boat's fine.

14:52.792 --> 14:54.167
I'm happy Kelsie,

14:54.167 --> 14:55.459
she's got the confidence
to come and wake me up.

14:55.459 --> 15:03.876
She understands
what's required of her.

15:03.876 --> 15:11.542
[alarm sounds]

15:11.542 --> 15:13.542
♪ Gary's gonna wash his hair ♪

15:13.542 --> 15:17.167
♪ He's gonna wash his hair,
wash his hair, wash his hair ♪

15:17.167 --> 15:25.792
♪ My hair's gonna feel clean ♪

15:25.792 --> 15:27.834
Mother----er!

15:27.834 --> 15:29.167
-Morning.
-Morning.

15:29.167 --> 15:30.792
That looks good.

15:30.792 --> 15:32.626
Brie, raspberry, and then
I put honey truffle on top.

15:32.626 --> 15:33.626
[bleep]

15:33.626 --> 15:36.000
-Good morning.
-Can I offer you some coffee?

15:36.000 --> 15:37.167
I'll take some coffee.

15:37.167 --> 15:41.375
-Sure.
-Awesome.

15:41.375 --> 15:44.959
Ooh... what was...
oh, gosh.

15:44.959 --> 15:46.876
Good morning.

15:46.876 --> 15:51.417
There was a wasp.

15:51.417 --> 15:52.667
Good, Jane.

15:52.667 --> 15:55.834
Here we've got fritatas with
spinach, onion, and cheese.

15:55.834 --> 15:56.959
Oh, my God, that looks amazing.

15:56.959 --> 15:59.167
These are mini croque monsieurs.

15:59.167 --> 16:01.667
Here we have a brie croûte

16:01.667 --> 16:04.125
with brie, raspberry,
and honey truffle on top.

16:04.125 --> 16:05.584
Son of a...

16:05.584 --> 16:08.876
Pastries, bread, bacon,
vegan bacon, hash browns...

16:08.876 --> 16:10.167
Oh, my God, there's more?

16:10.167 --> 16:12.959
I'm going straight
for the bacon.

16:12.959 --> 16:14.584
So good.

16:14.584 --> 16:16.709
If you and Colin have time, you
could work on the talent show.

16:16.709 --> 16:18.751
What does everyone wanna do,
like, sing a song?

16:18.751 --> 16:21.375
As long as it doesn't
have to be a good voice.

16:21.375 --> 16:22.792
Like, give me a line,
like,

16:22.792 --> 16:24.292
♪ Oh, here's the fruit ♪

16:24.292 --> 16:25.709
That actually
sounded really good.

16:25.709 --> 16:27.751
Nothing's off the table
in yachting.

16:27.751 --> 16:30.375
♪ Oh, ahoy, stand back

16:30.375 --> 16:31.959
-Oh, ahoy.
-Oh, ahoy.

16:31.959 --> 16:32.959
We're not on a pirate ship.

16:32.959 --> 16:34.584
We could be.

16:34.584 --> 16:38.667
You pretty much can ask the crew
to do anything except sex.

16:38.667 --> 16:41.167
And I've been offered
money for sex before.

16:41.167 --> 16:44.876
We can't choreograph
a musical and work.

16:44.876 --> 16:51.751
[laughing]

16:51.751 --> 17:02.751
[text chimes]

17:02.751 --> 17:04.751
[sighs]

17:04.751 --> 17:07.292
For this boat to operate
effectively and safely,

17:07.292 --> 17:10.709
I need every crewmember
to be on their A game.

17:10.709 --> 17:13.292
Tom has been
distracted and defensive

17:13.292 --> 17:15.167
since we dragged aground.

17:15.167 --> 17:24.959
What's a good excuse for that?
I can't think of one.

17:24.959 --> 17:27.918
For me, it's actually
better to be man down

17:27.918 --> 17:30.209
than risk it ever
happening again.

17:30.209 --> 17:32.000
He's not giving me what I need.

17:32.000 --> 17:38.042
He's not taking advantage
of that small opportunity.

17:38.042 --> 17:44.167
[sighs]

17:44.167 --> 17:45.584
Tom, Tom, Tom, Glenn.

17:45.584 --> 18:03.626
Meet me in the crew
mess, please.

18:03.626 --> 18:03.626
Come on down here.
Let's have a seat.

18:03.626 --> 18:15.125
They're not seated yet, right?

18:15.125 --> 18:19.584
Okay, Tom, you know,
I've had a little bit of time

18:19.584 --> 18:23.167
to think about this,
and it's quite clear

18:23.167 --> 18:27.459
that it took us quite
a long time to drag.

18:27.459 --> 18:30.375
I have no understanding
of how you couldn't notice it

18:30.375 --> 18:31.918
if you're on anchor watch.

18:31.918 --> 18:34.250
To me, it's impossible, it's...

18:34.250 --> 18:37.959
The whole point of anchor
watch is precisely

18:37.959 --> 18:39.584
to make sure that
doesn't happen.

18:39.584 --> 18:41.876
And I feel bad, and I
have no pleasure in this,

18:41.876 --> 18:44.250
but you know, the more
I think about it...

18:44.250 --> 18:45.918
It's okay, don't worry
about it, Glenn.

18:45.918 --> 18:49.792
Yeah, I have to let you go.
I got no choice.

18:49.792 --> 18:51.751
Just let me say it while
I'm here in front of you.

18:51.751 --> 18:52.959
That is not myself.

18:52.959 --> 18:55.751
I've been going through some
things, as you know, that...

18:55.751 --> 18:56.876
I know that.

18:56.876 --> 18:59.375
And that really did affect me
in what's going on.

18:59.375 --> 19:01.167
I understand that.

19:01.167 --> 19:03.209
It's really clear to me that
Tom's mind is in another place.

19:03.209 --> 19:05.584
So, it's not like we can
just let him stay

19:05.584 --> 19:07.292
because he can't do any harm.

19:07.292 --> 19:10.250
He can still do harm
in that mindset.

19:10.250 --> 19:12.584
We're not here
to provide a job for Tom.

19:12.584 --> 19:16.125
We're here to run a safe boat.
That's gotta be first.

19:16.125 --> 19:18.792
Well, I'm sorry it couldn't
have worked out better.

19:18.792 --> 19:23.083
It is what it is.

19:23.083 --> 19:24.626
Oh, my God.

19:24.626 --> 19:27.125
Get your stuff ready, because
I think I'm gonna

19:27.125 --> 19:30.792
have a ride for you in about
an hour, hour and a half.

19:30.792 --> 19:32.209
-Yeah.
-Cool?

19:32.209 --> 19:34.751
-It is what it is.
-All right, man, thanks.

19:34.751 --> 19:36.209
I feel like this is gonna
be one of

19:36.209 --> 19:37.834
the biggest lessons
in my whole life.

19:37.834 --> 19:40.667
I just wanna start
this whole season again,

19:40.667 --> 19:43.000
and just do a
----ing better job.

19:43.000 --> 19:44.459
You can't slack in this game.

19:44.459 --> 19:47.375
I've learned that the hard way.

19:47.375 --> 19:49.584
Yeah, I've gotta go.

19:49.584 --> 19:52.042
It's a shame,
but it is what it is.

19:52.042 --> 19:53.584
I'm sad to leave you guys.

19:53.584 --> 19:55.918
Yeah, well, bro,
you're gonna grow with this...

19:55.918 --> 19:57.626
-Yeah.
-Definitely.

19:57.626 --> 19:58.375
I have to.

19:58.375 --> 20:00.501
Yeah, you have to,
yeah, yeah.

20:00.501 --> 20:10.876
Yeah.

20:10.876 --> 20:13.501
Gary, Daisy, and Colin,

20:13.501 --> 20:15.751
can you guys meet me up
in the wheelhouse?

20:15.751 --> 20:17.751
Copy that, on my way.

20:17.751 --> 20:19.542
-Hi, Tom.
-H
i, Mum.

20:19.542 --> 20:20.959
-How are you?
-B
een better.

20:20.959 --> 20:22.375
I have to leave, basically.

20:22.375 --> 20:23.876
I'm not allowed to stay.

20:23.876 --> 20:26.209
It's too big of an incident
to sort of ignore.

20:26.209 --> 20:29.918
-It was, you know...
-Oh.

20:29.918 --> 20:33.083
Yeah, I'm...

20:33.083 --> 20:35.417
Yeah.

20:35.417 --> 20:38.167
I just wanted to have a quick
word with you guys about Tom.

20:38.167 --> 20:40.417
If there was a way I could
keep him I would have,

20:40.417 --> 20:42.959
but I can't trust him,
and we just can't afford

20:42.959 --> 20:46.334
to have somebody on board
that we can't trust.

20:46.334 --> 20:49.167
We are gonna be
a little bit short.

20:49.167 --> 20:50.834
Now, I hope to
get his replacement

20:50.834 --> 20:52.167
on before the next charter.

20:52.167 --> 20:54.584
In the meantime, Colin,
if I could ask you

20:54.584 --> 20:56.375
to help out a little
bit more on deck,

20:56.375 --> 20:58.751
and then you can take up
some of Tom's slack.

20:58.751 --> 20:59.959
Okay, we can make it work.

20:59.959 --> 21:01.959
Yeah, we're all just gonna
have to chip in, all righty?

21:01.959 --> 21:03.334
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

21:03.334 --> 21:08.709
Cool

21:08.709 --> 21:11.375
Let's get ready
to rumble on the watersports

21:11.375 --> 21:20.000
I wanna do that.
They have, like, a float.

21:20.000 --> 21:21.375
-Hello.
-Hi.

21:21.375 --> 21:23.000
I hope you don't hold
any hard feelings.

21:23.000 --> 21:27.167
No, we're good.

21:27.167 --> 21:29.000
I know. I know.

21:29.000 --> 21:32.375
We've literally loved and hated
each other this whole trip.

21:32.375 --> 21:34.209
I hope that we can be
friends one day properly.

21:34.209 --> 21:35.292
You know, I hope
we can look back at this

21:35.292 --> 21:36.792
and just laugh at it.

21:36.792 --> 21:38.709
I am gonna miss you,
but it's just, like,

21:38.709 --> 21:41.834
I feel like this is probably,
like, the best thing.

21:41.834 --> 21:45.501
I have learned to never
have sex with a woman

21:45.501 --> 21:48.667
who wants to have sex
with your boss.

21:48.667 --> 21:52.167
-All right, thanks, Ashley.
-Bye, hon.

21:52.167 --> 21:59.417
This could be
Tom's ride coming now.

21:59.417 --> 22:02.918
No!

22:02.918 --> 22:04.000
-Love you, man.
-Love you.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.918
Take it easy.

22:06.918 --> 22:08.959
I didn't wanna let anyone
down on the crew,

22:08.959 --> 22:12.167
but I've just been up and down
like a yo-yo, like, constantly.

22:12.167 --> 22:13.792
I'm actually leaving the boat,

22:13.792 --> 22:15.125
just for some stuff
going on back home.

22:15.125 --> 22:17.083
-Oh, that makes us sad.
-Oh!

22:17.083 --> 22:18.167
-Boom.
-Take care of you.

22:18.167 --> 22:19.876
-Yeah.
-You take care of you.

22:19.876 --> 22:21.375
Good luck with everything.

22:21.375 --> 22:24.792
But definitely need to listen
to people more and to...

22:24.792 --> 22:27.125
not to act on my emotions.

22:27.125 --> 22:28.125
-It's been real, bro.
-Take care, man.

22:28.125 --> 22:29.375
I will.

22:29.375 --> 22:30.667
Look after yourself,
keep in touch.

22:30.667 --> 22:35.876
But it's time for me
to say goodbye.

22:35.876 --> 22:39.167
Well, that was unexpected.
That's sad.

22:39.167 --> 22:40.876
Really good life lesson for him.

22:40.876 --> 22:46.417
Big time.

22:46.417 --> 22:48.501
What do I do, what did I miss,
what's happening?

22:48.501 --> 22:50.501
-Feel so out of the loop.
-Jesus...

22:50.501 --> 22:51.918
All right, so, Tom's left.

22:51.918 --> 22:53.375
Yeah, just learned that.

22:53.375 --> 22:55.375
You can go down, if you want.

22:55.375 --> 22:56.918
Come up at 11:00.

22:56.918 --> 23:03.042
Aw, bye, Tom.

23:03.042 --> 23:04.751
We should have somebody by...

23:04.751 --> 23:08.542
by next charter, we should
have the full replacement.

23:08.542 --> 23:11.167
-Are you sad?
-Sad?

23:11.167 --> 23:12.417
I mean, I got a little,
like, teary-eyed.

23:12.417 --> 23:14.334
I mean, I don't, like...

23:14.334 --> 23:15.792
Yeah, we don't want
nobody to go.

23:15.792 --> 23:18.584
Well, let's see
how's the new boy.

23:18.584 --> 23:21.167
I ----ing hope it's someone
that Kelsie likes,

23:21.167 --> 23:23.542
someone that Gabriela likes.

23:23.542 --> 23:29.334
I'm done.

23:29.334 --> 23:30.542
We gotta work together
on this, then.

23:30.542 --> 23:31.542
Yeah, I know.

23:31.542 --> 23:34.000
I can jump in wherever.
What about the watches?

23:34.000 --> 23:35.209
Kelsie's on nights now anyway,

23:35.209 --> 23:36.667
so if you help me out
in the day,

23:36.667 --> 23:39.792
Even if I can make you have
a break during the day,

23:39.792 --> 23:48.083
put a chamois in my hand.

23:48.083 --> 23:49.542
Gary, we're gonna fire up.

23:49.542 --> 23:50.959
I'm gonna go change my shirt.

23:50.959 --> 23:58.000
You can start picking up.

23:58.000 --> 23:59.501
Anchor's home, anchor's home.

23:59.501 --> 24:01.125
Copy, anchor home, thanks.

24:01.125 --> 24:03.501
This is a good breeze, eh?

24:03.501 --> 24:06.375
Now that Tom's off the boat,
I really wanna get things

24:06.375 --> 24:08.167
back to normal as quickly
as possible

24:08.167 --> 24:10.292
to lighten the mood and
focus on making sure

24:10.292 --> 24:12.209
the guests have
the best experience possible.

24:12.209 --> 24:15.584
Gary, can you pitch up?
I'm gonna do the mizzen.

24:15.584 --> 24:16.709
Copy.

24:16.709 --> 24:17.584
Can I do it?

24:17.584 --> 24:19.375
I'm gonna try to
get everything away,

24:19.375 --> 24:22.959
because I'm worried we're
gonna heel hard.

24:22.959 --> 24:24.792
I feel like I kinda
know what I'm doing,

24:24.792 --> 24:25.959
but you make this look good.

24:25.959 --> 24:27.292
-Do I?
-Yeah, yeah.

24:27.292 --> 24:28.375
Well, thank you, thank you.

24:28.375 --> 24:29.959
To the deck, everyone.

24:29.959 --> 24:33.000
Let's go see what's happening
up there, I guess.

24:33.000 --> 24:34.000
How's that?

24:34.000 --> 24:36.167
Boom, you're there.

24:36.167 --> 24:39.375
Okay, main.

24:39.375 --> 24:40.751
Sorry it's so windy.

24:40.751 --> 24:42.000
I just moussed my hair,
I don't know

24:42.000 --> 24:43.000
what you're talking about, pal.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.792
That's it, yep.

24:44.792 --> 24:47.501
-It's getting serious now.
-Let's haul out the genoas.

24:47.501 --> 24:53.083
I don't like these cabinets.

24:53.083 --> 24:54.834
And you're good.

24:54.834 --> 24:58.876
Oh!

24:58.876 --> 25:02.542
We are moving!

25:02.542 --> 25:05.584
Holy cow!

25:05.584 --> 25:07.918
Ah!

25:07.918 --> 25:09.834
Nice, I like excitement.

25:09.834 --> 25:11.167
Yeah, nice job, Colin.

25:11.167 --> 25:12.959
Dear baby Jesus.

25:12.959 --> 25:14.083
Coming up...

25:14.083 --> 25:15.584
-Ready whenever you are.
-Oh, yeah?

25:15.584 --> 25:17.209
-Yeah.
-When you told me that?

25:17.209 --> 25:19.125
I thought Gabriela
came down and told you?

25:19.125 --> 25:20.876
Where's our food?

25:20.876 --> 25:20.876
Oh, ----ing..

25:20.876 --> 25:29.417
Okay, Tom, you know,
I've had a little bit of time

25:29.417 --> 25:36.501
Oh, yeah, yeah.

25:36.501 --> 25:38.876
[bleep] me!

25:38.876 --> 25:40.375
That's what we
should be doing, is, like,

25:40.375 --> 25:42.042
a pots-and-pans band
for our talent show.

25:42.042 --> 25:43.375
I can do that.

25:43.375 --> 25:45.709
Yeah, but that's
what we should be doing.

25:45.709 --> 25:48.709
See, that would be fun.

25:48.709 --> 25:50.584
Gary, if you want, we'll put
that lazy sheet away now.

25:50.584 --> 25:51.584
Okay, copy.

25:51.584 --> 25:53.959
Well, Ken, I guess you
could call the mizzen.

25:53.959 --> 25:59.667
Yes, sir.

25:59.667 --> 26:01.083
Good.

26:01.083 --> 26:05.459
We're gonna go to four.

26:05.459 --> 26:07.375
That's four shots, four shots.

26:07.375 --> 26:11.167
-Copy, thanks, mate.
-Whew, okay.

26:11.167 --> 26:12.709
Dinner is at 9:00.

26:12.709 --> 26:14.167
You're on dinner
service tonight.

26:14.167 --> 26:15.918
Cool.

26:15.918 --> 26:18.375
I don't know what to do about
this ----ing talent show.

26:18.375 --> 26:20.959
You know I used to be a
professional dancer, right?

26:20.959 --> 26:22.209
What kind of dancing did you do?

26:22.209 --> 26:23.751
-Samba and salsa.
-Oh, cool.

26:23.751 --> 26:25.125
That would be good.

26:25.125 --> 26:28.042
I grew up dancing salsa
since I was, like, five,

26:28.042 --> 26:29.626
so I was born for this.

26:29.626 --> 26:32.334
When I first moved to L.A.,
I ended up getting picked up

26:32.334 --> 26:34.209
on a professional samba team,

26:34.209 --> 26:35.834
and my instructor asked me
to assist him

26:35.834 --> 26:38.792
on his private salsa
lessons with celebrities.

26:38.792 --> 26:40.083
So, I got this.

26:40.083 --> 26:43.292
Ahh... yeah.

26:43.292 --> 26:44.334
I think they would love that.

26:44.334 --> 26:45.501
Yeah, they would.

26:45.501 --> 26:47.417
You wanna brainstorm ideas?

26:47.417 --> 26:51.000
Does any of us have
any talent? You.

26:51.000 --> 26:52.209
Zero.

26:52.209 --> 26:54.125
You do play guitar.

26:54.125 --> 26:55.876
So, Daisy and
the girls dance.

26:55.876 --> 26:57.959
You're the headlining act,
with a...

26:57.959 --> 26:59.751
-Yeah, I'm...
-He's gonna tell a joke.

26:59.751 --> 27:02.584
-That's gonna be the highlight.
-Highlight.

27:02.584 --> 27:05.167
Say, hey, guys, we're all
gonna do a 20-second slot.

27:05.167 --> 27:06.834
So, this is all you get.

27:06.834 --> 27:08.459
Everyone can laugh and applaud,
then we move to the next one.

27:08.459 --> 27:10.792
That's it, done.
Easy-peasy.

27:10.792 --> 27:12.709
Okay, the tender's good.

27:12.709 --> 27:14.459
That's about it,
